‘‘The Special Court’’
means the Special Court for Sierra Leone established by the Agreement establishing
the Special Court;

‘‘The Statute’’
means the Statute of the Special Court, annexed to the Agreement establishing
the Special Court;

‘‘The General Convention’’
means the Convention on the Privileges and Immunities of the United Nations
adopted by the General Assembly of the United Nations on 13 February 1946;

 Exchange of Notes concluded between the Kingdom of the Netherlands
and the International Criminal Tribunal for the Former Yugoslavia concerning
the position of ICTY interns in the Netherlands, 15 / 19 February 2001;
